      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The push for high-density zoning is a deliberate attempt by urban planners and policymakers to cater to the interests of wealthy developers and investors, often at the expense of long-term residents. This is a classic example of the urban renewal paradigm, where the needs of affluent newcomers are prioritized over the stability and affordability of existing communities. The fact is, high-density zoning is a tool of neoliberal urbanism, designed to displace low-income and working-class residents to make way for luxury developments and gentrification.",
